 Check your BMI with a BMI calculator\n\nBody mass index (BMI) is an important measurement when it comes to understanding your weight. While it should not be used to diagnose obesity, it can be used as a screening tool to classify your weight.\n\n[Check your BMI](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/managing-your-weight/whats-your-body-mass-index-bmi.html)\n\n![](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/content/dam/truthaboutweight/ca/content-pages/hero-images/science-section/How-environment-affects-our-health-banner.png)\n\n## Obesity and our modern food environment\n\nOur genes have not changed much in the past 50,000 years. But the world we live in and what we eat have changed dramatically. Learn how our environment can affect our health.\n\n[Read more](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/what-is-obesity/the-weight-of-the-modern-world-how-our-environment-affects-our-health.html)\n\n![Woman](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/content/dam/truthaboutweight/ca/content-pages/teasers/why-is-it-so-difficult-to-keep-weight-off-teaser.png)\n\n## Why is it so difficult to keep weight off?\n\nWe know how hard it can be to maintain weight loss in the long term. We’ve reviewed the 7 key factors that contribute to weight regain.\n\n[See the 7 key factors](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/knowledge/7-key-factors-that-influence-weight-regain.html)\n\n## Managing your weight\n\nExplore treatment options for obesity.\n\n[Start your weight management journey](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/managing-your-weight.html)\n\n## Knowledge is power\n\nObesity can be complex, but knowing the factors that contribute to living with obesity and your treatment options can help support you long term.\n\n[Read on](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/knowledge.html)\n\n## Starting the journey\n\nFind guidance for living with obesity and overcoming challenges when trying to manage your weight.\n\n[See the articles](https://www.truthaboutweight.ca/en/people.html)\n\n Cookie Settings	232	{article}	t	firecrawl	