ils>\n<div class="text parbase">\n\n<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://www.truthaboutweight.global/etc.clientlibs/wcm/foundation/clientlibs/accessibility.lc-6fe5d4427361a4c0ca5a75457e3e4256-lc.min.css" type="text/css">\n\n\n    \n</div>\n<div class="container responsivegrid">\n\n    \n    \n    \n    <div id="container-bea48cd254" class="cmp-container">\n        \n        <div class="text">\n<p>HQ24OB00504</p>\n\n\n\n    \n</div>\n\n        \n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n        \n    </div>\n\n</section>\n\n        \n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n    \n</div>\n</div>\n\n    \n</div>\n</div>\n\n    \n</div>\n</main>\n  \n</div>\n  \n    \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n\n    \n    \n    \n\n  \n  \n<button id="ot-sdk-btn" class="ot-sdk-show-settings">\n  Cookie Settings\n</button>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n</body></html>	[Go to the page content](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/#main)\n\n![Discover the Truth About Weight](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/content-pages/hero-images/homepage/v2/herobanner-new-desktop-image.png)\n\n# _Discover the_  _**Truth About Weight**_\n\nObesity is more than weight—it’s a complex disease that can be linked to serious health issues like cardiovascular disease. Take the first step toward better health by understanding the science of obesity.\n\n[Understanding Obesity: It's Not Just About Weight Loss](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/what-is-obesity/obesity-is-more-than-just-weight-loss.html)\n\n## Check your Waist-to-Height Ratio\n\nMetricImperial\n\nMetric /Imperial\n\nWhy do I need to calculate this?\n\nBMI can only screen for obesity, it can’t measure body fat distribution which may indicate one's risk of heart related conditions. For that you need to calculate your Waist-to-Height Ratio\n\nHeight\n\n\ncm\n\nWaist Circumference\n\n\ncm\n\nCalculate\n\n\nHeight\n\n\nft\n\nin\n\nWaist Circumference\n\n\nin\n\nCalculate\n\n\n![](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/content-pages/infographics/desktop/homepage-test-image1.png)\n\n## Your waistline tells a story about your health\n\nFat around the waist—visceral fat—can increase your risk of cardiovascular disease, even with a healthy BMI. Measuring your waistline gives you key insights to take control of your health.\n\n[Read more](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/what-is-obesity/your-waistline-measurement-can-estimate-your-heart-disease-risk.html)\n\n![](https://nn-product.videomarketingplatform.co/64968566/108772968/72320ba83766971aced7b0fcfa7f4dac/625xcr/thumbnail.jpg)\n\n![hearthealth-obesity-1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/hearthealth-obesity-1.gif)\n\n## Test your knowledge\n\nAre you curious to understand the link between obesity and heart health? Take this quick quiz to find out their connection and prevalence around the world. Discover facts about these diseases and test your knowledge.\n\n[Take the quiz](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/what-is-obesity/obesity-and-heart-health.html)\n\n![](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/content-pages/infographics/desktop/home-test-new-design-image2.png)\n\n## Speak your heart out\n\nWe understand that discussing obesity and weight is not easy. That’s why we have created a guide to help you have an open and meaningful conversation with your health care provider.\n\n[Find your guide here](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/obesity-and-your-heart-a-guide-for-meaningful-discussions.html)\n\n## You’re not lazy, obesity is a complex disease\n\nManaging weight isn’t as simple as eating less and moving more. Genetics, environment, and other factors all play a role in your weight and the development of obesity. You’re not alone in this. See how others are taking charge of their health.\n\n[Watch more stories about obesity](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/inspiration-for-change.html)\n\n![verden-v1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-1.gif)\n\n## +1 Billion\n\nPeople are living with obesity worldwide, highlighting the complexity of the disease and the urgent need for comprehensive obesity care.\n\n![](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-2.gif)\n\n## 40-70%\n\nOf the risk of developing obesity can be attributed to genetics, highlighting that it's not just about willpower but also biological factors.\n\n![mand-v1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-3.gif)\n\n## +200\n\nObesity is associated with more than 200 health complications.\n\n![measuring-tape-v1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-4.gif)\n\n## <0.5 ratio\n\nFor a healthier heart, your waist should be less than half your height.\n\n![hjerte-v1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-5.gif)\n\n## 5%\n\nReduction in excess weight can improve heart health and quality of life.\n\n![vaegt-v1](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/gif/icon-6.gif)\n\n## 2.9 x\n\nPeople living with obesity are 2.9 times more likely to achieve their weight management  goal when working with an obesity expert.\n\n![Discover the Truth About Weight](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/content-pages/infographics/desktop/homepage-test-card-image2-v1.png)\n\n## Managing your weight\n\nExplore scientifically-proven obesity management options and make a plan to meet your goals.\n\n[Start your weight management journey](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/managing-your-weight.html)\n\n![Discover the Truth About Weight](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/content/dam/truthaboutweight/shared/content-pages/infographics/desktop/homepage-test-image-card-v1.png)\n\n## Join the Community\n\nDiscover a reliable source for all things obesity and connect with like-minded people on your weight management journey through our newsletter.\n\n[Get inspired to take the first step](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/join-the-community.html)\n\n## **Find your local weight management provider**\n\nTalk to your weight management provider about treatment options that could prevent the weight you lose from coming back.\n\nSelect your country\n\nSelect your country\n\nArgentina\n\nAustria\n\nBrazil\n\nChile\n\nColombia\n\nCroatia\n\nGermany\n\nItaly\n\nMalaysia\n\nPoland\n\nPortugal\n\nRomania\n\nSaudi Arabia\n\nSingapore\n\nSlovakia\n\nSpain\n\nUAE\n\n[Find now](https://www.truthaboutweight.global/global/en/managing-your-weight/hcp-locator.html)\n\n###### References:\n\n01. T-P-3166: A systematic review and evaluation of current evidence reveals 236 obesity-associated disorders\n02. Lopez-Jimenez, F. _et al._ (2022) ‘Obesity and cardiovascular disease: Mechanistic insights and management strategies. A joint position paper by the World Heart Federation and World Obesity Federation’, _European Journal of Preventive Cardiology_, 29(17), pp. 2218–2237. doi:10.1093/eurjpc/zwac187.\n03. Ashwell, M. (2011) ‘Charts based on body mass index and waist-to-height ratio to assess the health risks of Obesity: A Review’, _The Open Obesity Journal_, 3(1), pp. 78–84. doi:10.2174/1876823701103010078.\n04. Powell-Wiley, T.M. _et al._ (2021) ‘Obesity and cardiovascular disease: A scientific statement from the American Heart Association’, _Circulation_, 143(21). doi:10.1161/cir.0000000000000973.\n05. Lau DCW, Wharton S. Canadian Adult Obesity Clinical Practice Guidelines: The Science of Obesity. Available from: [https://obesitycanada.ca/guidelines/science.](https://obesitycanada.ca/guidelines/science. "https://obesitycanada.ca/guidelines/science.")\n06. NCD Risk Factor Collaboration (NCD-RisC). Worldwide trends in underweight and obesity from 1990 to 2022: a pooled analysis of 366